12/09/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The spokeswoman for EU security chief Javier Solana said Thursday (11 September) that the Union is convinced that the Macedonian government has the right to do what is necessary to re-establish the rule of law across the country. 
In an interview with Radio Free Europe, Christine Galah added that the mandate of the EU military mission to Macedonia would end as scheduled on 15 December.
Also Thursday, Interior Minister Hari Kostov announced that he has ordered his security and intelligence agencies to outline concrete measures to be taken to arrest two leaders of the rebel Albanian National Army, blamed for recent unrest in north western Macedonia.
In other news, a Macedonian military delegation is in Albania to discuss the strengthening of bilateral co-operation, in view of the Adriatic Charter signed by Albania, Macedonia and Croatia to co-ordinate preparations for NATO membership. 
(Utrinski Vesnik - 12/09/03; MIA, A1 TV, ATA - 11/09/03)
